{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.12",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 12,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 12",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 12 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:2",
      "text": "So then ye alone are men, and wisdom shall die with you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:3",
      "text": "But I also have a heart as well as you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:4",
      "text": "For a righteous and blameless man has become a subject for mockery.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:5",
      "text": "For it had been ordained that he should fall under others at the appointed time, and that his houses should be spoiled by transgressors: let not however any one trust that, being evil, he shall be held guiltless,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:6",
      "text": "even as many as provoke the Lord, as if there were indeed to be no inquisition made of them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:7",
      "text": "But ask now the beasts, if they may speak to thee; and the birds of the air, if they may declare to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:8",
      "text": "Tell the earth, if it may speak to thee: and the fishes of the sea shall explain to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:9",
      "text": "Who then has not known in all these things, that the hand of the Lord has made them?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:10",
      "text": "Whereas the life of all living things is in his hand, and the breath of every man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:11",
      "text": "For the ear tries words, and the palate tastes meats.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:12",
      "text": "In length of time is wisdom, and in long life knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:13",
      "text": "With him are wisdom and power, with him counsel and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:14",
      "text": "If he should cast down, who will build up? if he should shut up against men, who shall open?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:15",
      "text": "If he should withhold the water, he will dry the earth: and if he should let it loose, he overthrows and destroys it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:16",
      "text": "With him are strength and power: he has knowledge and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:17",
      "text": "He leads counsellors away captive, and maddens the judges of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:18",
      "text": "He seats kings upon thrones, and girds their loins with a girdle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:19",
      "text": "He sends away priests into captivity, and overthrows the mighty ones of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:20",
      "text": "He changes the lips of the trusty, and he knows the understanding of the elders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:21",
      "text": "He pours dishonour upon princes, and heals the lowly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:22",
      "text": "Revealing deep things out of darkness: and he has brought into light the shadow of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:23",
      "text": "Causing the nations to wander, and destroying them: overthrowing the nations, and leading them away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:24",
      "text": "Perplexing the minds of the princes of the earth: and he causes them to wander in a way they have not known, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.12.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:25",
      "text": "Let them grope in darkness, and let there be no light, and let them wander as a drunken man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
